  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6ad60c8 2022-12-20T00:03:55.959118247Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script script/poc.s.sol --ffi\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHi there, for weird reasons, ffi commands run from solidity scripts are executed multiple times.\r\n\r\nHere is a PoC example:\r\n```solidity\r\n/* poc.s.sol */\r\n\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.17;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract RunFfi is Script {\r\n    function run() external {\r\n        string[] memory inputs = new string[](3);\r\n        inputs[0] = \"python3\";\r\n        inputs[1] = \"script/_python/script.py\";\r\n        bytes memory res = vm.ffi(inputs);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# script.py\r\n\r\nimport sys\r\nfrom eth_abi import encode\r\n\r\nwith open(\"script/_python/test.txt\", \"r+\") as f:\r\n    n = int(f.read())\r\n    print(f\"Call {n}\", file=sys.stderr)\r\n    f.truncate(0)\r\n    f.seek(0)\r\n    f.write(str(n+1))\r\n\r\nenc = encode([\"uint256\"], [1])\r\nprint(\"0x\" + enc.hex())\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nRunning `forge script script/poc.s.sol --ffi ` outputs the following:\r\n```\r\ndeveloper@645d22a985c4:/com.docker.devenvironments.code$ forge script script/poc.s.sol --ffi\r\n[тав] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.118460Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 0\\n\"\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.229839Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 1\\n\"\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.340024Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 2\\n\"\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.452011Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 3\\n\"\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.565023Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 4\\n\"\r\n2022-12-20T17:37:22.673120Z ERROR foundry_evm::executor::inspector::cheatcodes::ext: stderr err=\"Call 5\\n\"\r\nScript ran successfully.\r\nGas used: 29208\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis shows that the ffi command is called 6 times which is a bit problematic when the command is expensive to run.",
